DENGUE - INDIA (NORTH)
**********************
A ProMED post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Dengue/DHF - India (10) 961115173601
Dengue/DHF - India (11) 961115204518
Dengue/DHF - India (12) 961129231255
Dengue - India (02) 970927201510
Dengue - India (Haryana) 981016204721
Dengue - India (Maharashtra) (04) 980918004225
From: ProMED
Date: 25 September 1999
Source: The Hindu (newspaper), 24 Sep 1999 [edited

September and October are considered the peak season for the transmission
of dengue [viruses in India. As part of the efforts to maintain the
momentum of preventive measures against the disease, the Health Ministry
convened a high-level meeting in New Delhi on Wednesday that was attended
by senior officials of Delhi and the 3 neighbouring States of Uttar
Pradesh, Haryana and Rajasthan.
So far, 33 cases have been reported in the region: 24 in Delhi, 6 in Uttar
Pradesh, 2 in Haryana and one in Rajasthan. Of the cases in Delhi, 6 came
from Uttar Pradesh and 2 from Haryana.
